# Linux Text Processing

## Commands Covered

- grep
- wc
- sort
- uniq
- cut

## Purpose

These commands help administrators search logs, filter information, count entries, and extract useful data.

## Common Usage

```bash
grep error logfile

wc -l file

sort file

sort file | uniq

cut -d ":" -f1 /etc/passwd
```

## Best Practice

Combine commands using pipes (`|`) to perform efficient text processing.
